<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Lake Bonavista</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Lake Bonavista was the first community in Canada to be built surrounding a man-made lake,
                acting as a
                prototype for further lake community developments in the country. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Surrounding two beautiful lakes (Lake Bonavista to the North and Lake Bonaventure to the
                South), Lake
                Bonavista homes are located nearby the beautiful Fish Creek Provincial Park and crested by the majestic
                prairie sky. </p>
            <p class="par-xl">Not only a wonderful place to raise children, but also a hot spot for outdoor recreation
                with easy
                connectivity to shopping and services.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Developed in the 1960s by Kelwood Corp, the Lake Bonavista real estate includes three
                different levels of
                properties.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">The community includes a 52-acre man-made lake built in 1968 to add to the natural beauty
                of the
                location. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">The lake and the Fish Creek Park provide a host of recreational opportunities besides
                offering pleasant
                views from the homes. The highest price for homes in Lake Bonavista Estates is $4 million, while the
                average price is $685,000.</p>


        </div>
